canonical:
  title: 思箴
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 我卒作事悔不思之思而後行寧有禍隨我卒吐言悔不復思思而後吐寧有辱追思之勿遽遽則多違思之勿深深則多疑商酌折衷三思最宜
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 思箴
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 我卒作事。悔不思之。思而後行。寧有禍隨。我卒吐言。悔不復思。思而後吐。寧有辱追。思之勿遽。遽則多違。思之勿深。深則多疑。商酌折衷。三思最宜。
korean:
  title: 사잠
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 내가 갑자기 일을 하고는 생각하지 않는 것을 뉘우친다. 생각한 뒤에 일을 하였다면 어찌 화(禍)가 따라 오겠는가. 내가 갑자기 말을 하고는 더 한번 생각하지 않은 것을 뉘우친다. 생각한 뒤에 말을 하였더라면 어찌 욕됨이 따라 붙겠는가. 생각하여 경솔히 하지 말라. 경솔히 하면 어긋나는 것이 많으니라. 생각하기를 너무나 깊게 하지는 말라. 깊게 하면 의심이 많게 된다. 참작하고 절충하여 세 번쯤 생각하는 것이 가장 적당하다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0520_030_0030&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Reflection on Deliberation
  author: Lee Gyubo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I have acted without thought, and now regret that I did not pause to consider.
    Had I reflected before acting, would calamity have followed in my wake?

    I have spoken in haste, and now regret that I did not think again.
    Had I reflected before speaking, would shame have clung to my words?

    When you deliberate, do not rush through hastily—
    rushedness breeds discord and error.
    When you deliberate, do not sink too deep in thought—
    too much depth breeds doubt and suspicion.

    Weigh all sides with balance and measure;
    to think three times over is wisdom's perfect gate.
  footnotes:
    - The threefold deliberation mentioned in the final lines reflects classical Chinese philosophy on balanced judgment—neither impetuous nor paralyzed by overthinking.
